Task
To take an umbrella or not to take?
The variable rain is given, containing one of two values: true or false. Get the message: 
"It is raining, take an umbrella" or "You can leave the umbrella at home".
Create a rain variable and give it a boolean value of true or false. Create an advice variable. 
Using the if-else command, get the advice variable to: "It is raining, take an umbrella" if rain = true, "You can leave the umbrella at home", otherwise.

Solution
const rain = true;
let advice;
if (rain) {advice = 'It is raining, take an umbrella';} else {advice = 'You can leave the umbrella at home';}
